## Code Style

### General
- Use 2-space indentation for HTML, CSS, JavaScript, JSON, YAML
- Use 4-space indentation for PHP
- Maximum line length of 120 characters
- Use single quotes for strings unless interpolation needed
- Always use strict equality (=== and !==) in JavaScript
- Prefer const over let; avoid var entirely
- Use meaningful, descriptive variable and function names

### HTML
- Semantic HTML5 elements (nav, main, article, section, aside, footer)
- Always include alt attributes on images
- Use lowercase for element names and attributes

### CSS
- Prefer modern CSS (custom properties, grid, flexbox)
- Mobile-first media queries (min-width)
- BEM naming convention for custom classes

### JavaScript
- ES6+ features (arrow functions, destructuring, template literals)
- Async/await over raw promises
- Early returns to reduce nesting

### PHP
- PSR-12 coding standards
- Type declarations for parameters and return types
- Null coalescing (??) and nullsafe operator (?->)
- Early returns to reduce nesting

## Security

- Sanitize all user input before output
- Use parameterized queries for database operations
- Never commit credentials, API keys, or secrets
- Escape output appropriate to context (HTML, JS, URL, SQL)

## Git

- Conventional commits: type(scope): description
- Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, style, test, chore
- Imperative mood ("Add feature" not "Added feature")

## Documentation

- Comment the "why," not the "what"
- Use JSDoc/PHPDoc for functions
- Keep README files current

## Testing

- Write testable code: pure functions, dependency injection
- Test behavior, not implementation details
- Cover edge cases and error conditions
